'''霜凍作用'''是一種[[風化作用|風化作用]]，是指[[岩石|岩石]]的孔隙中的[[液态水|液態水]][[結冰|結冰]]後，冰的體積日益龐大，岩石受到冰塊擠壓而破裂<ref name="Goudie">{{Cite book|last=Goudie|first=A.S.|last2=Viles H.|title=5: Weathering Processes and Forms|editor-last=Burt T.P.|editor3=Chorley R.J.|publisher=Geological Society|year=2008|series=Landforms or the Development of Gemorphology|volume=4|pages=129–164|isbn=9781862392496|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=wg0Rl7dY5ZYC&q=frost-shattering&pg=PA137|access-date=2020-11-18|archive-date=2021-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210816210141/https://books.google.com/books?id=wg0Rl7dY5ZYC&q=frost-shattering&pg=PA137|dead-url=no}}</ref>。地處潮湿的[[温带|温带]]地区的裸露的岩石，特别是多孔岩石，如[[砂岩|砂岩]]，極易出現霜凍作用現象。

